    <title>Leetcode exercise</title>
    <link href="/2021/10/20/Leetcode-exercise/"/>
    <url>/2021/10/20/Leetcode-exercise/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="Oct-20"><a href="#Oct-20" class="headerlink" title="Oct 20"></a>Oct 20</h3><p><strong># 28. Implement strStr()</strong></p><p>There is a time exceed problem. Try this tomorrow.</p><p>===</p><p>My original code was like:</p><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title">Solution</span> </span>&#123;</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="keyword">int</span> <span class="title">strStr</span><span class="params">(String haystack, String needle)</span> </span>&#123;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> (needle.length() ==<span class="number">0</span>) <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="number">0</span>;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> (haystack.length() == <span class="number">0</span> || (needle.length() &gt; haystack.length())) <span class="keyword">return</span> -<span class="number">1</span>;        </span><br><span class="line">        String tmp = haystack;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">int</span> i=<span class="number">0</span>;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">while</span> (tmp.indexOf(needle) != <span class="number">0</span>) &#123;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> (i&gt; haystack.length() - needle.length()) <span class="keyword">return</span> -<span class="number">1</span>;</span><br><span class="line">        i++;</span><br><span class="line">        tmp=haystack.substring(i);</span><br><span class="line">        &#125;</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>This is a stupid solution since indexOf already gives the first index of needle.</p><p>Now my solution is:</p><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title">Solution</span> </span>&#123;</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="keyword">int</span> <span class="title">strStr</span><span class="params">(String haystack, String needle)</span> </span>&#123;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> (needle.length() ==<span class="number">0</span>) <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="number">0</span>;</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> (haystack.length() == <span class="number">0</span> || (needle.length() &gt; haystack.length())) <span class="keyword">return</span> -<span class="number">1</span>;        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> haystack.indexOf(needle);</span><br><span class="line">    &#125;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><strong># 704. Binary Search</strong></p><p>I used a simple binary search, <code>left&lt;=right</code> and update mid with <code>mid=left+(right-left)/2</code>to avoid overflow.</p><p><strong># 35. Search Insert Position</strong></p><p>similar to last question, when <code>nums[mid]&lt;target &amp;&amp; nums[mid+1] &gt; target</code> should return <code>mid+1</code> . If to use method 2, <code>left &lt; right</code>, then <code>left</code> should be updated as  <code>left=mid+1</code> and right should be updated as <code>right=mid</code>. </p><p><strong># 34. Find First and Last Position of Element in Sorted Array</strong></p><p>write <code>getLeftborder</code> and <code>getRightborder</code> separately.</p><p>对于helper分三种情况</p><p>==</p><p>4 in total</p>]]></content>
    
    
    
